The statement\nproposed\nthe progress\nLabor-Management i\n\u2018It would be socially undesirable to\njeopardise the gains achieved by pnet*\npitating new causes at strike and Al\nwill, the Bishops said.\nThe statement concluded with thasa\nwords:\n\u201cWe think it la high time to intro*\nduce sound ethical standards into all\nphases of our economy. The present\npreoccupation with 'Right TO Woek*\nlaws may ho good occasion for all our\nleaders in the field at labor and to\nthe field of management to\ntheir consciences as to their bonaat\nmotivation, their Meals, and thair\npractices. _\u2019\n\u201cAs to the present lama brfenlL\nelectorate in Ohio, we a\nthat a \u2018Bight-to-Work*\nwould hot Mbe our\nnhght lead to a\nstruggle for domination and\naa era of\nschool construction program\nincome tax cut.\nThe\nly was having its\nCanada with 8S4.544\ned for\n20 per cent of the I\nThe Dominion Bureau at Statistics\nreported that average weekly\nand hours were down la\ncast of the crumpled\n8omii Tht Nttoon hones\nTfcnsi A 8\u00abturduy string f>\u00a3\nHie desk where Mr. Nelson opened\nbills and wrote a letter to the electric\npaiiy, protesting against their adyertising\nthat electricity gives more value for every\ndollar than any other item in the family\nbudget\n2 Where Mr. Nelson looked at die electric\ndock to see if he had time to mail his letter\nbefore dinner.\n3 The hi-fi set he turned off as he left\nroom.\n4 Where Mr. N. paused to check the\nnace thermostat and turn on the porch light\nto guide the dinner guests.\n3 His daughter\u2019s bedroom where he\nwatched her drying her hair with the\ntrie hair dryer and admired die\nhad just ironed for her date.\n4 The TV, with Junior riding herd.\n7 The electric coffeemaker and die\nready to do dinner duty.\n3 The all-electric kitchen, where dinner\ncooking and Mrs. Nelson was taking\ncubes from die refrigerator\u2014and where the\nelectric dishwasher and clotheswasher and\ndryer were waiting to do the chores ahead.\n9 The bade porch, where Mr. N. paused to\nthink\u2014realising that his family wat putting\nelectricity to work in doaens of ways all\never the house... ways he often forgot Se\nmaybe the electric company was right about\nthe value of his service.\n10 The trash can into\nIMWiATION\nKRMA CONSTRUCTION COt.\nL\u2014Jng m* ton\u2014\nBBSS\n7'jy #V_","height":"25696","width":"20256"}}
